Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of secure transmission over a Gaussian two-user MISO broadcast channel, which involves information theory (IT) and cryptography (CR). The use of network topology and channel state information at the transmitter (CSIT) suggests that it may also fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (NI) and systems and control (SY). The encoding scheme mentioned in the abstract also hints at the possibility of multimedia (MM) applications.
